post_title: ENDED- Brown Old Mills For Sale
post_content:
I have decided to end this listing and keep the 3 left/available that went unsold/disposed of. For the sake of community and tracking, the examples below have found new homes. In addition to the three I am keeping, I decided to also keep my Greminger and to consign to Memory Lane my Cy Young ghost, multi-strike, brown old mill.  

Kiernan - SOLD
Helm - SOLD 
Jordan - SOLD
Revelle - SOLD
Paige - SOLD
Bernhard multi-strike SOLD
Cy Young Ghost, multi-strike  consigned
Don’t let the sheer quantity of Ryan’s brown OM throw you off.  40 years of collecting tells me that are as rare as everyone says.  I feel lucky to have one in my collection.

I am in the line of worshipers- truly incredible, Ryan!

 Trent King
One of the best BST listings I have ever seen, you will NEVER see this many of the toughest back available ever again.

Also although the Violat was a private transaction.  It was in dad and my collection for around 2 decades - we somehow got INSANELY lucky to find one that we thought MAY be brown listed on eBay - before it was as popular as it is today.  I had already been wrong around half a dozen times at this point … but was definitely not wrong once the card arrived.  I only traded it to Ryan Bc he had a dupe BOM for our collection.  I have zero concern about its authenticity and apparently SGC agrees.  So for those who want a “Hank and Scott” pedigree rareback - this is your chance :)

Happy collecting everyone.

Not to be overly dramatic, but I echo what’s been said and alluded to above…this is a once in a lifetime BST post. The cards are stunning and incredibly rare, and Ryan is as solid as it gets.

Fantastic event, congrats and good luck Ryan!

Thanks for the kind words all.
, 
5 are gone and 4 remain.  As mentioned in the initial post, given the cost/value, I am willing to allow payment over time with a meaningful deposit/down payment.

Hi Ryan,

Amazing cards. Is Kiernan still available?

Chris
Yes Chris, and per our texts and PMs, he is yours at $22k. I will get it out via FedEx Monday. Thanks!
Bump for update.  I will not bump again for a 1-2 weeks
